            <thetext>Hi

Here is a short description of the problem.

Situation:
We use &quot;qx.ui.list.List&quot; and I set selectionMode to &quot;multi&quot;. Now we select all items in list. I expected that if I now click one item, all other items will be unselected (like in table), but this is not the case.

So the main problem:
Once the user has selected all items, there is no way to unselect them again.

There are 2 ways around this, but most users do not find it:
1) If you hold the &quot;Ctrl&quot; key and unselect one item, then you can release the &quot;Ctrl&quot; key and click the unselected item. This will then finally unselect all items in list.
2) If you click the first item in list, then the items will be unelected correctly.

Example:
http://goo.gl/aeRvL8</thetext>
